Oracle Feels Confused

by ratakim

You wake up (with a bad taste in your mouth) to the smells of summer: flowers, grass and fresh cat pee. You get up and look around. You are in a closed yard. Next to you is a bench. On the bench sleeps a man who surely looks like an old drunkard.

You tap him on the shoulder to wake him up. He slowly wakes and tries to focus his eyes on you. "Hello there! Must have been another wild night in Cowsala! Don´t remember anything. Who the hell are you?" he asks.

You introduce yourself. He nods and says: "Pleased to meet you! I am Ratakim Seesnocolors, the Oracle of Youhitburg. Some call me Grandpa Huntsnot (don´t know why, I absolutely love meat), others Grandpa Climbsnot or even Grandpa Stiff, but they are the stupid people from the Land of Mockery east of here."

He grabs a can from the ground, shakes it listening to it, then drops it.

"I am the Solver of Mysteries, Summoner of Demons, Picker of Combination Locks, Hacker of Phone Booths (or once was) and a well known Seer. My visions often come while asleep...and nowadays I mostly sleep...must be getting old. I´m also famous for my ability to communicate with animals. Long ago I lived in the great city of Vanda. The inhabitants, called vandals, revered me as the greatest squirrel whisperer of all times."

Through a gate comes a big tomcat with the back end of a small rabbit dangling from his sharp teeth. "Speaking of animals, here comes one. May I introduce you to my familiar, Hellcat. He is the slayer of mice, moles, grey partridges, ducks, adders and rabbits. He hunts for all of us so there´s always meat on the table." The cat devours a rabbit leg in three big bites and drops the other one at Oracles feet.

The Oracle takes a pause and then continues. "Lately I got sick. Some brain-eating disease. My wife, Mrs Muggle, managed to get me into a program where I was chosen to test an experimental drug called Works Three Ways. I got a year's supply of meds in a dispenser, but didn´t start taking them right away. My bad!
My mind got even mushier and I forgot how to use the dispenser. Shortly after that my wife got fed up with me and moved to live with her mother in Buckburg. I need those meds to get my head cleared and my wife back. Can you please help me?"

He goes through his pockets. "Nice! I probably lost my key last night."

The Courtyard

High walls rise to north, west and south. There is a big gate in the western wall leading outside. To east is a door to a two-story mansion. Above the door is a sign. A tower rises from the roof of the mansion at one corner. There are some flowerbeds here and a bench. The Oracle sits on the bench and a big tomcat sleeps in his lap. There are a few empty beer cans on the ground beside them.  There is a rabbit leg here.
> take rabbit leg

> take rabbit leg
You pick it up.
> tell cat to open door

> tell cat to open door
The cat looks at you for a long time, then gets up and stretches his muscular body. He walks to the door and goes in through the flap. You can hear his nails scratching on the door handle and in a bit the door swings and stays open. He comes out and looks at you again as if to tell you it wasn´t so hard you couldn´t do it yourself. He then jumps on Oracle's lap and falls asleep again.
