When you enter the library the first thing you see are thousands of books stored neatly on numerous shelves. The Oracle must be really keen on reading and books. When you examine the shelves you quickly see that the books are organised by subject and under that in alphabetical order by the authors and under that in chronological order.

You spot some of his favorite authors: Stephen King, J.R.R. Tolkien and William Gibson. There is a wide collection of fantasy novels based on the role-playing game Advanced Dungeons & Dragons. In the same category there are some manuals to the game also, for example  the Unearthed Arcana.

The Library

The room has no windows and you guess it´s because they would have limited the number of bookshelves. All the walls are covered with shelves from the floor to the ceiling.
And the books, there must be thousands of volumes! They are organized by subject, author and chronological order. You understand that it would be very easy to find a particular one.
On the floor is a large persian rug and in one corner an armchair with a reading lamp next to it.
> move rug

> move rug
With a big effort you move the rug aside and reveal a hatch in the floor.
