The West End of the Nukeproof Shelter

This is every preppers wet dream! A fully equipped nuclear device proof shelter under your own house. In this end are the living quarters. There are bunk beds for ten, liquid gas-powered cooking devices and heaters, sofas, tables and chairs, toilet and bathroom facilities, a TV set with a VHS player and a large collection of VHS tapes. There is also a "command center": a desk with a Commodore 64 computer on it. Beside the computer there is a floppy disk drive and in front of it a small old TV. Above them on the wall are several surveillance camera screens. In one of them you can see the Oracle in the courtyard picking his nose and shaking and listening to the empty beer cans again. You suddenly understand that this prehistoric technology is propably immune to a possible EMP blast. To east is seen a big storage area and you can make out two dirt bikes there.
