You walk along the road and meet a couple beside a white motor home making pea soup on a portable stove. There is a name Penelope painted on the side of the motor home.

The man says "Hi! I'm mr Deweys and this is my wife mrs Deweys, together we are Team Deweys." You tell your name and he continues "We visited grandma Deweys in Cowsala and now we are going to the cabin to play some board games with aunt Deweys. My notorious cousin Al Depone cancelled at the last moment, something about an incoming shipment and the police."

They offer you some soup and the three of you have a nice lunch together. Mr Deweys speaks non-stop and you listen eating your soup. After you have eaten they pack their vehicle again, bid you farewell and drive off towards west. "What a nice couple!" you think looking after them.

