The Lake

You paddle with all your might but this kayak is shit and the waves are too high and you can only go south to the boathouse or west along the shore.
> west

> west
You paddle along the shore and come across a couple in real kayaks, not cheap inflatable ones. A noble-looking man inspects your Barbara with scorn and says "Good day to you! I am Sir Sprucebranch and this is Lady Goldfinches." "European Goldfinches" says the woman and continues "I would give you a little curtsy but it's quite difficult in a kayak."

 Sir Sprucebranch takes a concerned look at his phone and says "The hunt is on and there are several new hits in the checker, we must go now!" Lady Goldfinches nods at you "It was nice to meet you, but now we must go. Stay near the shore, that is not a real kayak!"

 You watch them paddle towards a little island in the distance and wonder: they spoke about a hunt, but all they had with them were fishing rods?

